File: Schools are set to open for Grades 12 and 7 on Monday. JOHANNESBURG - Judgment on the urgency of the reopening of schools case will be heard on Wednesday. The Educators Union of South Africa filed an urgent application to overturn the reopening of schools. READ: Unions welcome reopening of schools Should it succeed over 26,000 public and independent schools will have to close again. However, Solidarity is arguing in favour of opening schools. Grade 7 and 12s went back to class on Monday in government's phased reopening. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.